HEADWORD: Soubrette
<hw>Sou`brette"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>A female
servant or attendant; specifically, as a term of the theater, a lady's
maid, in comedies, who acts the part of an intrigante; a meddlesome,
mischievous female servant or young woman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soubriquet</ent>⟦br⟧
